<div class="page-width page-content">

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="grid__item medium-up--three-quarters medium-up--push-one-eighth">

      <header class="section-header">
        <h1 class="section-header__title">
          {{ page.title }}
        </h1>
      </header>

      {%- if page.content != blank -%}
        <div class="rte rte--nomargin zenkai-policy__intro">
          {{ page.content }}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="rte rte--nomargin zenkai-policy">
        <p class="zenkai-policy__lede">Small brand. Real people. Here's exactly how we handle things when something isn't perfect.</p>

        <h2>If it arrives damaged or misprinted</h2>
        <p>We replace it, free. <a href="/pages/contact">Send us a message</a> with a photo and we'll get a new one on the way. You don't need to ship the damaged one back.</p>

        <h2>If you're not happy with your first tee</h2>
        <p>You have 30 days from delivery to request a refund on the first item in your first order. No interrogation, no photos — just reach out.</p>

        <h2>Additional items in the same order</h2>
        <p>For anything beyond that first tee, we handle it through exchange or store credit, not cash. This keeps the shop sustainable — each piece is printed fresh when you order, and a full refund on a printed multi-item order is a loss we can't absorb as a small operation.</p>

        <h2>If the size is off</h2>
        <p>One free size exchange per order. If you're trading up a tier that costs more, we just ask you to cover the difference.</p>

        <h2>Shipping, always</h2>
        <p>Free in the US, always. Most orders ship in 1–2 business days. You'll get tracking the moment it goes out.</p>

        <hr>

        <p class="zenkai-policy__why"><strong>Why the policy is shaped this way:</strong> each Zenkai tee is printed fresh when you order it — nothing warehoused, nothing mass-produced. That means we can't restock returns, and a full-order cash refund on printed goods isn't something we can absorb while still making good tees. The promises above are the real ones — the ones we can keep without gimmicks or cutting corners on quality.</p>

        <p>Questions before you order? <a href="/pages/contact">Contact us</a> — we answer every email.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</div>

